review_text:
People today are too comfortable with technology, and we’ve become too reliant on convenience. These dishwashing tablets are a perfect example of that. They make life easier, yes, but they also take away the experience of washing dishes by hand. There’s something valuable in that task—when you wash dishes manually, at first it feels annoying, but over time, you start to realize what a privilege it is to have the ability to clean your own plates. Not everyone has can have dirty dishes. Washing dishes by hand brings a sense of empathy and humility that these tablets just erase. It’s easy to forget the things we should be thankful for when we let machines do all the work. I believe we could all benefit from returning to doing things ourselve
Sometimes it’s those simple, everyday tasks that remind us of how fortunate we really are.

review_text:
Using this the air in my flat does smell cleaner. Helps to get rid of the food smell after cooking. My friend with allergies usually had problems when he visited but now its all good :D

My disappointment is from the noise. Its okay that when its going full blast it will be noisy, I understand that... but the "silent" bed time mode is NOT silent. It is quiet but the fan speed is not constant, it pulses every 1/4 second to keep the fan spinning and that pulse is very annoying. I have to turn it off at night or when I study. To be fair if you are talking to people or have the tv on you won't notice it.

Also the only time the air quality bar changed color and made the fan faster was then the garden service came and mowed the lawn. Otherwise its always on green. So I have to manually put it on full blast for a while. 

Edit: the air quality changed when I burned some food in the frying pan. It went to red and went real fast for a while, by the time it was green, the burned food smell was gone.

I tried to set up the app, I got confused and uninstalled it :/

review_text:
If you’ve ever stayed at a fancy hotel and thought, "Wow, this sheet feels expensive," then good news—this is it! The Hospitality Collection 144TC White Flat Sheet brings that crisp, clean, and fresh hotel vibe straight to your bedroom.

Soft, Smooth & Breathable
The 144 thread count might not sound like Egyptian cotton levels, but don’t let the numbers fool you—this sheet is lightweight, breathable, and ridiculously comfortable. It keeps you cool in summer and cozy in winter, making it the perfect all-season bedding choice.

Crisp & Clean Look
The bright white color gives your bed that elegant, "freshly made by housekeeping" look. It’s simple, classic, and goes with any duvet or bedding set. You know, for when you want your bedroom to look like you have your life together.

Easy to Wash, Hard to Ruin
This sheet washes beautifully and doesn’t lose its shape or softness over time. Plus, it dries quickly, so you’re not waiting forever to make your bed again (because let’s be real, remaking a bed is already hard enough).

If you love hotel-quality bedding without the 5-star price tag, this flat sheet is a must-have. Now, if only it came with someone to make my bed every morning…

review_text:
Alas it did not end well - radio started very good but after a few weeks the blue wire (amp switch) stopped working draining the battery - then it started randomly turning off and on. I returned the radio.
Original review: I replaced my Sony X-plod double Din radio with this unit as I needed the Bluetooth function. Sound quality is no less than the old unit - volume is good and the added features are a bonus. The old unit had the option to lower the output to the RCA plugs (for the amp to the Subwoofers) - this one does not, so you need to lower the gain on the amp. The final effect is the same. The only real issue is the lack of the mounting bracket - fortunately I had the one from the old radio (which I modified to fit the new radio). I read the complaints in some of the other reviews and can only surmise that the persons doing the installation did not know what they were doing as it works perfectly. As to the fact that the radio turns off when reversing (I added a reverse camera ) - I believe this is a safety feature. All in all, I would definitely recommend this radio as it is actually AWESOME, and punches way above the price.
product_title: Car Radio 2 Din HD Touch Screen Multimedia Player 7 Inch Screen

review_text:
Short: Extremely comfortable. Fits perfectly. Cold is a thing of the past. Spend the money, you won't be sorry.

Long: I've always wondered what differentiates my cheaper pair of sneakers or such to the ones worn by rich people and always thought that shoes are shoes are shoes (or in this case slipper boots). So when I got a cash injection recently, and as it would be my cheaper boot slippers were busy tearing at the seams and with Winter coming up I knew I had to get something new, so I decided to splurge and I have not been sorry for a single second.

I've had various boot slippers before, and wool skin slippers as well and they always tear at the seams, or the wool becomes so squished it's like walking in a normal pair of work shoes without socks. Now I've not had these, or the opportunity to wear them, too long to judge that aspect yet, but the times I have worn them has been absolute bliss.

These are super comfy, fit perfectly and you can just feel the quality in the material and the way it was made (hand made as well, and with attention to detail may I say). Previously when I had woolen slippers I would slip my feet out every 30mins or so as they'd get too warm (even mid-winter), but these I were able to wear the whole day with my feet nice a warm (not a single cold spot anywhere) but yet, strangely enough for wool slippers, not too warm that I'd start sweating and get uncomfortable. 

The only down side is my wife told me I am now not allowed to get a thick cotton robe and pretend to be Hugh Hefner... So this winter my feet will live in luxury while the rest of me freezes over.
product_title: Gurmuki MEN'S Sheepskin Wool Ankle Boots - 2Tone Navy

Pros:

Durable rubber coating

Non-roll hex design

Great value for the quality

review_text:
Really love the look of the door. It gives that industrial vibe. I think it is good value for money. The door is very sturdy.

I managed to install it, but I would say it is not a trivial process. Things that are good to know:
- The rail sits in the groove at the top of the door (to guide it). The stoppers made no sense to me so I just removed them and came up with another way to keep the door from de-railing.
- We decided to buy a different bottom door guide, that attaches to the wall instead of the floor (we did not want to drill into our floor tiles).
- When following the instructions for attaching the top wheels to the door, they give the wrong drill bit size. They gave 8mm bolts, not 6mm like they claim in the instructions, so I needed an 8mm wood drill bit. Also, make sure the rail fits easily into the space between the wheel and the door before you drill those holes. You do not want the spacers at the back of the rail grazing the top of the door. We did not exactly follow the suggested measurements here.
- You need a 10mm concrete drill bit (with a hammer action drill) to attach the rail to the wall. NOTE: It sat on the concrete lintel of our door, which is a pain to drill into (with the steel reinforcements). Make sure you have a tough enough drill bit for that part. Also, drilling into a lintel is not always advised, since it is structural, so maybe consult someone on that before buying this door.
- You should probably get some clear varnish to treat the door.

It is safest to attach the rail last. Get the whole thing working on the ground and then enlist some help to hold it in place so you can visualize and decide on the rail height.

Hope this helps.
product_title: K Brace Pine Barn Door- Interior Barn Sliding Door Including Mechanism

review_text:
Not very, but I'll try my best.

This cable has been a splendid addition to our household. It is not only functionally reliable, but has character.

It strikes a wonderful balance of being accessible when necessary, while still maintaining a certain degree of independence. It mostly just hangs around, assessing the situation, and then delivers power exactly as needed only when it is plugged in. Interestingly, it does not seem to charge my devices when not required. This demonstrates what I believe to be a fascinating insight into the situational awareness of these cables, which typically goes uncelebrated.

Unfortunately, it does have a tendency of going missing. I wish that it would stop doing so, but it does have the common decency of accepting accountability for it once confronted, and extends reparations by laying dead still until moved. I commend the cable for this. This is a trait that my dog does not seem to be capable of, and it is far more intelligent than this cable.

OK seriously now - the cable is great, and I can highly recommend.

review_text:
Nutritech quality and consistency in their product and flavor profile on point. 

You need to figure where this fits into your protein needs as it’s not a premium whey replacement doesn’t have the amino profile for the workout chug. It’s not a vegan alternative either and being almost as low carb and “light” as whey it’s not going to make a good even lean meal replacement alone. 

Now that’s not a bad thing - I think it’s use case is quite clear and necessary - a lean source of protein with a full amino acid profile (although inferior to premium whey), a good anytime lean protein to source to hit your daily protein intake while costing half the price of whey and definitely being a more environmentally friendly source in regards to the industry. 
Mixes well, easy on the tummy, cheap, sustainable and tastes good. Very useful for the above and once you figure out how it fits in to your specific dietary needs.

review_text:
Possibly the most cost-effective way to share USB devices between two computers, at the time of writing. Easy to understand and set up.

The switch-over between your two computers isn't instantaneous, but is quick enough to not be troublesome. One down-side is that the computer that is switched from, will react as if all of the USB devices have been disconnected.

Take note that this switch doesn't carry your display or monitors, only USB cables. I have successfully switched keyboards, mice, drawing tablets and USB headsets with this switch, all without issue.

However, take care to plug in the extra provided power cable, if any of your USB devices require charging, or otherwise consume more power due to RGB or similar. If a battery is accidentally charged through this switch, and it can't supply enough power, it will temporarily disable that specific USB port automatically to protect itself.

I own two of these switches, and both work perfectly. Highly recommended!
product_title: USB 2.0 KVM Switch Box 2-in-4 Out SE-L92

review_text:
This fan has impressed me with how unproblematic it has been considering that it did not break the bank. I found it easy to put together (I’m good at following instruction pamphlets), and it does its job brilliantly and very quietly. We leave it on all night in the summer and as a bonus, the breeze makes it harder for the mosquitoes to fly. Such an upgrade from the fan-less lifestyle! In appearance it’s nice and simple, I just wish it didn’t have a logo on it, I have yet to get around to painting over it. (I don’t like to pay for something that contains an ad. If it has a brand name plastered on it, it should be free in my opinion, or you can pay me to have it!)

My only other feedback/complaint, is that the front shield should be easier to remove so one can regularly clean the blades, which naturally gather dust from use and just over time. With this fan you have to remove a screw to take off the shield to clean the blades. I guess it’s a safety precaution for if you have kids, or for anyone who has not heard any “unsafe use of fan” horror stories.
product_title: Goldair - 40cm Oscillating Pedestal Fan

review_text: Much, much better than those various cheap-n-nasty flexi-spout versions out there. This is solid, all-metal, easy to swivel and simply a good nozzle! Fits my standard Cobra kitchen sink tap spout. It has the 2 settings, spray and stream - easily selected by twisting the main end piece. There is quite a bit of flow restriction though (water saving), even if the flow/aerator filter is removed, so if you want the original full high pressure, this is probably not for you. It certainly does the job though - the spray easily rinses off food waste/debris and the aerated stream provides normal sink/kettle/pan filling. Would certainly recommend this over those other nasty nozzles.
product_title: Faucet Aerator Tap Nozzle Extender 360 Swivel Kitchen Sink Faucet Sprayer

review_text:
I bought the Apple Watch SE as a gift, thinking it would be a decent entry-level Apple product. I was wrong. This thing is a glorified fitness band with Apple’s logo slapped on it—overpriced, underpowered, and utterly disappointing.

Battery Life? More Like Battery Death

The battery is a disaster. Apple claims "all-day battery life," but that’s only true if you never actually use the watch. My friend charged it to 100% before bed, and by midday, it was already begging for a charger. If you dare to use GPS for a workout or stream music? Forget it—you’ll be lucky to get 8 hours. Even my five-year-old Fitbit lasts longer, and it cost a fraction of the price.

Worse, it charges painfully slow. While other smartwatches juice up in 30-40 minutes, this thing takes over an hour just to get halfway. What’s the point of a "smart" watch if it’s dead half the time?

The Screen Might as Well Be a Fossil (From the Stone Age)

The display is embarrassingly dim. Indoors, it’s passable, but step outside on a sunny day? Good luck seeing anything. You’ll be squinting, tilting your wrist like a madman, or just giving up entirely.

And why doesn’t it have an always-on display? Even $100 smartwatches have this basic feature. Instead, you have to awkwardly flick your wrist every time you want to check the time—like some outdated tech from 2015.

Missing Features? More Like Missing the Point

No blood oxygen sensor, no ECG, no temperature tracking—just a bare-bones heart rate monitor that cheaper brands do better. The software is laggy, apps take forever to load, and Siri might as well be asleep.

Final Verdict: A Garbage Gift

If you’re thinking of buying this as a present—DON’T. Your friend will either return it immediately or resent you for wasting their time. For the same price, you could get a Hauwei or a Garmin that actually works.

Apple should be ashamed for selling this trash. Zero stars if I could.
product_title: Apple Watch SE GPS Aluminium Case with Sport Band (44mm) - M/L

Please would Marketing add one more picture showing the side of the box illustrating the included accessories with casserole tray, all dishwasher safe?

review_text: I read the multitude of bad reviews that this poor pen received and was weary of trying it out, but I am glad that I did. I am using this pen together with Colgate Optic White Oxygen toothpaste. After 5 days I can see a noticeable difference. It's not huge, but my front teeth are definitely lighter. For everyone who said that it doesn't work, you need to click the pen about 20 times at first use to get the liquid to come out. For subsequent uses it is about 5 to 10 clicks. Also, you must dry your teeth before application as the liquid hardens the moment it touches another liquid. Then you must remember to wipe clean the applicator with a tissue and not wash it for the same reason. It feels weird on my teeth but it seems to be worth it.

review_text:
Got one of these for my room, and it works really well. Syncing to your Bluetooth is a bit weird, but is really a once-off thing.

I also investigated it from a security perspective, and it requires a weird 3-way handshake for authentication (Coded an app to change the color and such from my PC), so it's unlikely to get hacked. It does send some data off to a third-party server, but since it allows you to change it whilst not at home, that's rather to be expected. review_text:
I've never used to have issues.  For the first year of my pool, the kreepy did the job and maybe once in a while got stuck on the step.  The second year, the kreepy started getting stuck more often, especially on the light and by the jets (where I have Pool Skims installed).  This year, the kreepy has turned full moron, getting stuck in any place that has a slight bend, anywhere in the pool.  I have to get it loose at least once an hour.

Enter this cheap little Pool Popper.  The kreepy has only been running on it for about 6-8 hours, and it hasn't gotten stuck once.  One time I thought it got stuck by the Pool Skim since everything looked tangled, but as I got closer, it moved on and untangled itself.  I didn't have much hope for it given the bad reviews for it thus far, but for me it is already a 1000% improvement.

For reference, I have a 8m x 6m rectangular marbelite pool.
product_title: Pool Popper

Battery life is on the short side, on speeds 2 or 3 it will last 3 hours. On speed 5 you will literally see the battery counter fall every 30 seconds 😂 but you cannot practically use it at that speed, you really can't breathe if it's pointed at your face. Still recommended, wife loves it.

review_text: ESCELLENT value for money. Be aware, this thing is HEAVY (isn't that EXACTLY why one buys a cast iron skillet)? But the fact that it is so heavy is because it's really thick cast iron, not cast aluminium like many other frying panes are. So, it takes time to heat up, but once heated up it retains its heat. It really does justice to a medium-rare (or clutch plate cooked, if that's your preference) steak. Properly heated, and properly oiled, I have never had a steak stick to the pan. The enamel also sees to it that the pan cleans easy. Remember not to scour it with a metal pot scrubber or steel wool or you will damage the enamel. If you do have some of your meal sticking to the pan, let it cool down, put about 5mm layer of water and a squirt of dishwasher liquid in the pan and heat it on the stove till the water gently boils, then scrape the food scraps loose with a wooden spoon . Throw away the dirty water and wash the pan in your basin with clean water and dishwashing liquid. If you do find that the white inner surface of the pan has some discolouration, you can from time to time (NOT every time you used it) add a tablespoon of dry bicarb in the pan, then add a LITTLE bit of water to form a paste and then gently rub with a dishwashing sponge. Rinse and then wash with soap and water and dry it properly. Amazing value for money - comparable pans usually sell for 3 times this price. Just keep in mind that this pan does not come with a lid so if you do need a lid, you will need to buy one separately
product_title: French Cast Iron Enamel Frypan Fry Pan with Free Gift Oven Glove - Red

review_text:
Okay, so this Fitness Gym Towel with Pocket? It's like the superhero of gym accessories - it's got a secret identity as a regular towel, but then BAM! It's got a pocket. 

I used to dread the gym because, where do you put your phone? In your sweaty shorts? No thanks. But with this towel, I've got a spot for my phone right next to where I'm wiping off the bench press. It's like having a personal locker on your shoulder.

The pocket is surprisingly spacious; I've managed to fit my phone, keys, and even a protein bar in there. It's like having a mini gym bag without the bulk. And let's talk about the towel itself - it's absorbent enough to handle my sweat after a particularly enthusiastic session with the weights. 

But here's the kicker - during one intense leg day, my phone fell out of my pocket while I was doing squats. The towel caught it like a safety net. My phone was safe, and I got an extra core workout from laughing so hard at the absurdity of it all. 

If you're tired of juggling your stuff while trying to look like you know what you're doing at the gym, this towel is a game-changer. Five stars for functionality, convenience, and for adding a touch of comedy to my workout routine.
product_title: Fitness Gym Towel with Pocket - Teal

review_text: First off lets look at the positive. Build quality is excellent, dual suspension bonus. Got it at Sale price and has since gone up but still a very good deal as quality is apparent. Purchased this for my 11 year old and he is delighted with it. Doesn't state what tyre pressure to inflate in the manual but it does say so on the tyre which is 40 PSI. Had an initial problem after removing the bicycle from the packaging withe the handlebar assembly unit as it was impossible to fix in the correct position without disconnecting the front brake cable which was a little annoying but soon remedied.  Adjusting the front brakes was also a bit awkward but with persistence I got it right. Bike comes with a kickstand and although it doesn't say there are a couple of bolts on top of the down tube for mounting a air pump or water bottle which is not supplied. Preference would have been for disc brakes but at this price entry point would be too much to expect. This should last my son a good 5 years or so. Overall very happy with quality.

review_text: I was concerned about using paint stripper on my ABS fairings but this seemed to tick the right boxes so I decided to take a chance. Using an old fairing that I didn't mind loosing, I have tested it and it worked as well or even better than anticipated.  Spray on and immediately you can see it starting to work. Just have to find the balance between leaving it on too long and not long enough. Went through multiple layers of paint well after a couple of applications. Just don't leave it on too long that it dries. 3 to 5 minutes seemed to be the sweet spot. Had problems where I left it for half an hour. Also be careful about what you use to pull the peeling paint layers off. Scraper was a bit aggressive for the plastic. Next time I will use wire wool rather than a scraper to wipe off then wont have as much work smoothing divots out. Plastic is just so soft, not like working on a steel tank or panel.  This product works well if used sensibly. I do recommend it. Managed to get very acceptable results after sanding, spot putty  and painting the panel afterwards.

review_text:
I recently purchased the Kitchen Pretend Playset Cookware Playset 36 Piece B4325 in Blue, and I am quite dissatisfied with the product.

Firstly, the stove included in the set is too small, making it difficult for children to use it effectively during play. The overall quality of the playset is not up to par, with many pieces feeling flimsy and poorly made. Additionally, there are too many "gap filler" pieces that do not add any real value to the play experience.

Another issue is that the pieces do not fit back into the box once they have been taken out, making storage a hassle. Given these drawbacks, I believe there are better products available on the market that offer more value for the same price.

Overall, I would not recommend this playset and would suggest looking for higher-quality alternatives.

review_text:
I had been researching how to test lithium battery based devices for a few weeks and came across these style of load testers on an American website. I was incredibly thrilled to find this on Takealot and immediately snapped it up. Decent price and works incredibly well. Comes with a ton of different connection options for different batteries and devices. I have used this to test more than 50 x 12v Mini DC UPS's (from a very prominent brand here in SA) for my work as we issue them to staff and have a huge stack of older ones in storage. 

The instructions were decent enough for me to figure out how to configure and run a test and it's fantastic. Gives you an accurate load test of how many mAh's are still left. 

I haven't used all the features, like bluetooth and connecting directly to my PC via USB to pull test data. But for my usage I don't need to. I would highly recommend this to anyone who wants to test most battery types. Just pay attention to the maximum current and wattage as outlined in the description as you don't want to burn out this magic little device.
product_title: 180W DL24P 2.4 Inch DC USB Tester Electronic Load APP

Very usefull device to install on your BMX, Mountainbike, Racing cycle or even the still standing training bike.

It hooks up onto your current handlebars then gives you extra space to mount some more gear & this is also a built in powerbank. You can hook up a short USB cable to whatever gear you mount onto it.

It comes with 2 rechargeable battery's included.

You can mix and match your different gears to install onto the extra bar, maybe a USB Rechargable Bicycle Light, a Cellphone mount or perhaps a Gopro or two.


This also free's up some space on your normal handle bars for other things that you need closer to your hands, maybe like a Electronic Bell or perhaps Sideview mirrors.

Highly recommended and it doesn't add alot of weight to the ride.

review_text:
I'm excited to share my review of the Samsung Galaxy S24 FE 5G 128GB Dual Sim in Light Blue, paired with the Samsung Galaxy SmartTag2.

Design and Display
The Galaxy S24 FE boasts a stunning 6.7-inch display, perfect for streaming, gaming, and browsing.¹ The Light Blue color is sleek and sophisticated, making it a stylish addition to anyone's tech collection.

Performance
With 8GB of RAM and a powerful Exynos 2400e processor, this phone delivers seamless performance and fast charging capabilities. Whether you're a heavy gamer or a social media enthusiast, this phone has got you covered.

Camera
The triple camera setup, featuring a 50MP primary sensor, 12MP ultra-wide-angle lens, and 8MP telephoto lens, captures stunning photos and videos. From landscapes to portraits, this camera delivers exceptional results.

Samsung Galaxy SmartTag2
The SmartTag2 is a clever addition to the Galaxy ecosystem, allowing you to track your belongings, pets, or even your car.² With Bluetooth Low Energy (BLE) connectivity and a compact design, it's easy to attach and use.

Verdict
Overall, I'm thoroughly impressed with the Samsung Galaxy S24 FE 5G 128GB Dual Sim in Light Blue, paired with the Samsung Galaxy SmartTag2. With its stunning display, powerful performance, and clever camera features, this phone is a top-notch choice for anyone seeking a premium Android experience. The SmartTag2 is a thoughtful addition, making it easy to keep track of your belongings.

Pros:
- *Stunning Display*: 6.7-inch display perfect for streaming and gaming
- *Powerful Performance*: Fast charging and seamless performance with Exynos 2400e processor
- *Impressive Camera*: Triple camera setup with 50MP primary sensor, 12MP ultra-wide-angle lens, and 8MP telephoto lens
- *Clever SmartTag2*: Track your belongings, pets, or car with ease

Cons:
- *No major cons noted*
product_title: Samsung Galaxy S24 FE 5G 128GB Dual Sim - Light Blue + Samsung Galaxy SmartTag2

Decent set of magnifying glasses. Purchased for electronics work and will be perfect for my needs.

Light is not overly bright, but does very good job of lighting up the work area.

3.5x magnification is good, but focal distance is pretty short. But very good for detail work.
The 2.5x is ideal for my needs without having to hunker way down on the workpiece.

Not heavy on the head when in use and seems to grip well.

Selected this one over other similar models because of the rechargable battery. Much better than buying AAA batteries all the time.

Lenses can't be stacked so you only have 1x - 3.5x, but honestly if anyone is going beyond that the focal distance will be so short that you might as stick the thing in your eye.

Overall, very pleased with this item.
